survey_response.review_text: We had been consulting Dr. Yasmin for my wife ever since we planned for pregnancy and we are glad we took this decision. Being into High risk category her advice and medication has been extremely beneficial through out the period. Any words of appreciation will be less for the kind of advice, strength and support that she has provided us in all these months. Not only is she an expert in her area but is also very approachable, friendly and patient. She has always been available and responded to all our queries even in the wee hours. She goes an extra mile to understand the problems of her patients and provides the best solution. Our pregnancy wasnt a very smooth one but Dr. Yasmin ensured we were calmed down everytime we panicked. Even during the delivery process she was available at all times and ensured that the baby was delivered safely without causing any risk to the mother or the baby. We are blessed with a baby girl and we are thankful to Dr.Yasmin as it wouldn't have been possible without her support. We would definitely recommend her to all the future parents to be.

review.practice_name: Kinder Women's Hospital and Fertility Centre

survey_response.review_text: We started visiting Yasmin Mam in 3rd trimester. I must say it was the best decision. She answers every question very calmly and also gives constant feedback if needed. She will never be in hurry. She motivated and prepared me for normal delivery. Finally with the constant support of mam and team, I had vaginal delivery. Would definitely recommend everyone to visit her during pregnancy.

I am writing this review to express our gratitude and heartfelt thanks to Dr. Yasmin Imdad who has guided us (throughout my wife's pregnancy) for a successful normal delivery of our baby in the month of January. We began to consult Dr. Yasmin from 7th week onwards, found her very comfortable, friendly, approachable, allocating enough time for us to discuss the progress every time. She had been advising, analyzing and treating precautionary measures based on health and BMS status week by week for progressing normal delivery as we had expressed our interest towards the same at the beginning.

Also, she has guided through all the parameters and specifically dietary habits which will keep both mother and baby health in control from the first trimester. My wife had developed gestational diabetes during the 2nd trimester which can lead to over weight of the baby and less possibility for a normal delivery. Therefore, she had advised us to workout, follow a perfect diet to control diabetes to maintain good mother and baby weight as well as to monitor blood sugar level periodically at home through which we had controlled blood sugar level.

She prescribed medicines, tests and follow-up week-by-week to monitor and develop good health for mother and baby, we just followed her foot-steps which had led to labor pain on the day when we had completed 38 weeks, and the delivery pain progressed very well. Though it was very painful for my wife, our doctor advised and strengthened us at timely to deliver our baby in a span of 3-4 hours without going for an epidural (painless method).

She treated and provided the best care when my wife had developed swelling and opening in the episiotomy area after delivery, also she asked us to do certain home treatments which really worked well and led to speedy recovery.

Throughout, our experience with Dr. Yasmin Imdad was very great, safe, comfortable and satisfying in all the scenarios as we simply have to go with her guidance and treatments. We strongly recommend Dr. Yasmin Imdad with the best experience which we have had.

Dr. Yasmin Imdad, we sincerely thank you for caring, guiding and providing best care throughout and brought us to successful normal delivery as this was our first pregnancy and you have really made us very special. Thank you doctor :-)

review.practice_name: Kinder Women's Hospital and Fertility Centre

survey_response.review_text:
Yasmin doctor has been my Gynecologist since 2-3 years now. Her professionalism and connect with all her patients has been noteworthy…

My recent experience with her of delivering my second child after a Csec for my first one has been eventful.

VBAC was possible only because of her stern belief in me and her constant motivation. She guided me throughout my journey to have a healthy baby boy.

I have always been impressed by her simplicity & patience.

Her magical smile during all the consultations were healing and calming…

“Radhika you are doing great”- will be my favorite dialogue of yours

Yasmin Doctor- you will always remain my favorite!

On November 2019 I visited Dr. Yasmin for the first time and got assurance that I'm in a safe hand. I wanted a normal delivery and on june 2020 I delivered my baby normally under guidance of her. From beginning onwards she was very humble and supportive. **** ********* ******** *** ********** ***** ****** **** ******** I developed gestational diabetes but she made me calm for this and suggested necessary precautions and diet. She was monitoring my sugar level on phone every alternate day. During the covid situation she was always available on phone and was clearing all doubts regarding labor pain. On the time of delivery my husband was not with me as he got dengue and admitted to different hospital but just because of Dr. Yasmin I took decision to deliver on planned date of delivery by induced labor method in Rainbow hospital. She informed other doctors about my situation and Delivery went very smooth. Post delivery I got fever, she took my case very seriously and monitored everything until I got discharge. A very BIG Thanks to her, she made my pregnancy journey wonderful . I strongly recommend her for pregnancy and delivery.  😊😊

To start with we visited doctor Yasmin in Rainbow in  Nov 2019 in Rainbow for my wife Priyanka for pregnancy test . The very first interaction was so appealing that we were convinced that we were  in right hands and decided to stick with the doctor until delivery which eventually happened in July 2020 . Her friendliness, ability to hear out and provide right recommendations really makes her stands apart from others . We had made a request to doctor that we would like to normal delivery and she ensured that it happened despite of the fact that my wife became diabetic during pregnancy and child weight was on the higher side . Her timely diagnosis and right suggestions made the difference . The best part was her connect with the patient during the testing times because of covid situation , she remained available over phone watsapp for any queries .At last during the delivery day , she ensured that she is available for the delivery herself during mid night and kept following up with patient and duty doctors throughout her admission . I could not thank her enough for all she has done for us . I highly do recommend Yasmin Mam if you stay near ORR , marathalli or Whitefield and trust me you won't regret your decision . Thanks Anshu

Very happy and extremely satisfied.  I visited Dr Yashmin when I got to know that I am pregnant. She is a subject matter expert in Obs & Gynae. In-fact, the reason I decided to consult her was her qualification (member of Royal college of obstetrician and gynecologist). After meeting her, I found her patient friendly. She listens to patient and clearly explains the medical condition and treatment. Qualification blended with humility makes her a wonderful doctor.I visited her for complete duration of pregnancy till delivery and now for post delivery care. In the later phase of my pregnancy, I got Intrahepatic cholestasis of pregnancy and Gestational diabetes mellitus. She handled the situation with swift and confidence. She never gave a room for panic. Finally, I had a pre-term delivery and Doctor visited me in odd hours to make sure everything is going fine with me. She was continuously in touch via phone/whatsapp during my hospitalization. Dr. performed c-section after non progressing labor on Diwali evening and I was bless with a baby. I was touched by her commitment as a Doctor.Thank you Dr Yashmin Ma'am. Thank you very much.

" , it is an inclusive and sensitive way of asking questions. Sexual activity of a person doesn't depend on their marital status, new age gyanaecologists should understand this. We need more doctors like Dr. Yasmin Imdad.

survey_response.review_text: During my pregnancy the advice  given by Dr. Yasmin always came with a rationale on why she was recommending those particular things to do, which i found quite convincing and genuine. Doctors way of explaining complications during pregnancy OR pros and cons of doing some tests  was very good. She addresses all your concerns during clinic visit with relevant facts and examples so that it's easy to understand.

review.practice_name: Kinder Women's Hospital and Fertility Centre

survey_response.review_text: Dr. Yasmin delivered my baby girl at Kinder hospital in July, her expertise and guidance has been crucial to me and my husband as first time parents. She has seen me right through my pregnancy from the onset and even treated me for preterm labour at 26 weeks which was quiet scary for us nonetheless with her right treatment and medication I pulled through 37 weeks and delivered a healthy baby girl. I have never seen a Dr so empathetic, calm and explains the condition correctly to the point. Dr. Yasmin has years of experience and her way of dealing with patients atleast for us is something we are most grateful for.

****** *** * *** **** ****** * ***** ****we started to see her after my wife stepped in to her 2nd trimester, With every visit our confidence and positivity has only gotten higher.Never rushes, always cleared all the doubts (clearly explains all the complications and provides us with an answer) by giving us enough time. Even at the off times she is just a phone call/ message away. There were time when yasmin mam her self message us to check how my wife is feeling.As my wife has a history of premature delivery, yasmin mam made sure  it is not repeated this time and took all the precautions and made sure she completed atleast 38 weeks at the time of LSCS ( cesarean section ). Couldn't have been this easier without her.we are glad and lucky that we found her.

We came to know about Dr. Yasmin Imdad from the internet. After reading the reviews we decided to visit her for consultation. It was a tough decision to make in the 5th month of pregnancy. But we never regretted our decision. She is one of the best doctors I have ever met. Apart from having expertise in her field, she is very polite, listens to and answers all the queries one may have with patience, no matter how silly the question is. She makes everything understandable in very simple words. It was only because of her patience and support that I could have a normal delivery. I was totally confident throughout my pregnancy that I was in safe hands and never had to seek any second opinion from anyone. Apart from this, she also involves the husband equally in all the discussions which is very important from a husband's perspective. In conclusion, I would blindly recommend her name to anyone seeking an OBGYN consultation in Bangalore.
P.S. - She will always reply to your texts.

Dr. Yasmin has been our doctor throughout the pregnancy. We were impressed by her friendly approach and clarity of communication as we (1st time parents!) started on the journey. And immediately thereafter the lockdowns happened - She was always there virtually, to guide us through the various stages as well as recommending the necessary supplements and tests that we should get. Her approach helped put us at ease and helped us gain confidence. When we met her in-person after many months (as lockdown eased), it was like she has always been there ! She was reassuring and took excellent care as our baby arrived at full term. Even post that, she has never been hesitant to help us whenever we have a query or confusion. She is a thorough professional with a caring heart - Thank you Dr. Yasmin !

I started my Pregnancy check up with Dr.Yasmin during my 5th month after I moved to Bengaluru. I had a cervical stitch in my 4th month. Even though I had a risk of preterm labour ma'am handled the situation very calmly. she explained to me all the details with positivity. I felt safe and comfortable with her given my condition. She was available to me over phone during this lockdown period. I delivered healthy baby on 14th May,2020 through a planned C-section. Have no second thoughts for consultanting Yasmin maam. Definitely you will have a wonderful experience. Thank you maam for all your help and guidance. It really means alot.

I met Dr Yasmin when I visited Rainbow hospital for confirming my pregnancy in October 2019. From my first meeting itself I was struck by her calm demeanor and the way she explained all the details. She did not rush us and cleared every minor doubt. I faced a few health issues during the pregnancy but she was there every step of the way. During the lockdown I could not visit the hospital a few times but I never panicked because she was always available through phone calls and messages. I delivered a healthy baby boy through a planned caesarian in June 2020. She took equal care post delivery as well.

I would say I found very good gynecologist for my pregnency. Her expertise will make you to have trust on her easily. She will explain clearly the medical condition and the treatment in a simple manner. Though I got many complications one by one throughout my pregnancy including Gestational diabetes, had normal delivery at the end which was unexpected for me. For any problem she will suggest very precautionary steps to avoid further complications. She was continuously in touch via whatsapp. I am happy to recommend her for my beloved ones and for all without any hesitation. Thank you Dr. Yasmin Imdad

I and my wife  hearty Thanks to Yasmin Madam *** ********* ********* ** ** ***** **** **** ***** Since my wife pregnancy confirmed till delivery we have with madam only. When ever we visited for general check up Madam always listened all concerns and replied with heartfull smile. So friendly , smiley , very nice doctor. Soo kind, even suggested best hospital for baby delivery under my finance. Finally madam did Normal delivery at Rainbow hospital with greater flexibility. I would 100 % recommend Dr. Yasmin Imdad Madam for all Gynic probs. Thank you madam, ** **** ***** **  *** **** ****** *

We really had a great experience with Dr. Yashmin during my wife's whole pregnancy period. As we faced the covid situation in the 2nd trimester we got scared to visit the hospital, but she was always available in WhatsApp to clarify our issues. So the covid didn't impact us much because of doctor's friendly behaviour. Since starting we told her that we want to opt for normal delivery. So she used to take care of each and every problem which didn't lead us to c-sec and we had a healthy normal delivery on June 2nd 2020 as she promised. We are really grateful to her for staying so long in labour room when my wife was facing difficulty to push the baby. After 3 months of delivery also she has not changed and like before she is helping us now over phone. Still our parents are not here due to covid situation, but she used to guide us every single doubt whenever we have which is really appreciable. She even considered our 1st trimester USA reports in our starting days of visits to her which usually other doctors ignored and suggested us to do the testing in their hospital for clear report. Overall we had a great and wonderful journey with Dr. Yashmin and we would love to visit her again if required.
